WEBVTT

00:02.860 --> 00:05.113
Well...
See you after the break.

00:05.114 --> 00:06.702
What are you all doing
for Thanksgiving?

00:06.703 --> 00:08.137
I'm having
Andre's whole family over,

00:08.138 --> 00:09.572
though he'll be stuck
working at the stereo store

00:09.573 --> 00:10.640
for Black Friday.

00:10.641 --> 00:12.391
Oh, sure, you get to say that,

00:12.392 --> 00:14.927
but we're stuck
calling it "Jew Friday."

00:14.928 --> 00:18.430
Ugh, I'll be with my family,
fielding the same old questions.

00:18.431 --> 00:19.615
"How's community college?"

00:19.616 --> 00:20.600
"What's your major?"

00:20.601 --> 00:21.584
"Are those real?"

00:21.585 --> 00:22.718
My aunt's boyfriend.

00:22.719 --> 00:24.804
"Oh, my family's
a normal religion,

00:24.805 --> 00:26.372
"so I have to talk to them
for five minutes

00:26.373 --> 00:29.191
before I get a casserole
that's all marshmallow."

00:29.192 --> 00:30.176
That's you.

00:30.177 --> 00:31.377
Brainstorm.

00:31.378 --> 00:32.995
Why don't you all
come over to my house?

00:32.996 --> 00:34.130
I'll have plenty of food.

00:34.131 --> 00:35.097
- That would be great.
- Marshmallows.

00:35.098 --> 00:36.365
Sounds good to me.

00:36.366 --> 00:37.400
I was going to microwave
buttered noodles,

00:37.401 --> 00:38.634
but this sounds
equally promising.

00:38.635 --> 00:39.952
I'm in.
Oh, goody.

00:39.953 --> 00:41.537
Well, you know,
you're all welcome, of course.

00:41.538 --> 00:43.339
- I'm in.
- Or, you know, Jeff or whoever.

00:43.340 --> 00:44.440
Can't. Plans.

00:44.441 --> 00:45.775
Well, if you change your mind,

00:45.776 --> 00:47.526
I can't think of anyone
who would enjoy having you more.

00:47.527 --> 00:49.996
How-Dean, pilgrims.

00:49.997 --> 00:51.564
- Is that...
- John Wayne, yes.

00:51.565 --> 00:52.798
Oh, good, you got it.

00:52.799 --> 00:56.586
Anyhoo, I just thought
I'd mosey on over here,

00:56.587 --> 00:59.171
invite you all
to Greendale's annual

00:59.172 --> 01:01.824
Thanks-living
potluck dinner,

01:01.825 --> 01:04.860
where we remember all we have
to be thankful for.

01:04.861 --> 01:06.195
There may be a statistical link

01:06.196 --> 01:08.514
to enrollment at Greendale
and holiday suicide.

01:08.515 --> 01:10.132
- Oh.
- Just a shoelace...

01:10.133 --> 01:12.551
and belt-free night
full of fun.

01:12.552 --> 01:14.453
You should all drop by.

01:14.454 --> 01:15.588
Or Jeff.
Or whoever.

01:15.589 --> 01:16.672
Oh, he can't.
He has plans.

01:16.673 --> 01:18.024
Oh, right,

01:18.025 --> 01:19.191
you are spending Thanksgiving
with your father.

01:20.510 --> 01:23.012
I thought I told you
to stop reading my email.

01:23.013 --> 01:25.765
Yeah, well, I thought I told
you to stop keeping secrets.

01:25.766 --> 01:26.932
How am I supposed to keep track

01:26.933 --> 01:28.434
of what you tell me
in confidence

01:28.435 --> 01:29.719
and what I hear
through your walls

01:29.720 --> 01:30.819
with a glass to my ear?

01:34.023 --> 01:36.058
Fine.
Close your mouths.

01:36.059 --> 01:38.227
I'm having Thanksgiving
with my estranged father.

01:38.228 --> 01:39.195
Can we move on now?

01:39.196 --> 01:40.379
Makes sense.

01:40.380 --> 01:41.731
Jeff's at a point in his life

01:41.732 --> 01:43.633
where he needs a strong
father figure to come out to.

01:43.634 --> 01:45.868
Jeff, this is huge news.

01:45.869 --> 01:47.353
Huger news.

01:47.354 --> 01:50.022
Was this decision made after
our Halloween conversation?

01:50.023 --> 01:52.858
Yes, after.
Not because of.

01:52.859 --> 01:55.027
I'll take it.

01:56.246 --> 01:58.731
You had that teed up?

01:58.732 --> 02:00.616
When I say "thera,"
you say "pist."

02:00.617 --> 02:01.617
Thera...

02:01.618 --> 02:02.585
- pist.
- Thera...

02:03.587 --> 02:04.637
Thanks for the support, guys.

02:04.638 --> 02:07.523
Oh, the support has just begun.

02:07.524 --> 02:09.258
What do you want me to bring
to papa Winger's house,

02:09.258 --> 02:11.410
some vegan pumpkin pie?

02:11.411 --> 02:12.778
Britta, you're not coming.

02:12.779 --> 02:15.014
Fine, regular pumpkin pie.

02:15.015 --> 02:16.215
Jeff, you're going to need me

02:16.216 --> 02:17.950
when things get messy
and emotional.

02:17.951 --> 02:19.318
The only thing that's going
to get messy and emotional

02:19.319 --> 02:21.203
is Troy, when he realizes
there are yams

02:21.204 --> 02:22.388
underneath those marshmallows.

02:22.389 --> 02:24.390
I knew it was too good
to be true.

02:24.391 --> 02:26.976
Jeff, speaking not just
as your friend

02:26.977 --> 02:29.512
but as an avid
daytime TV watcher,

02:29.513 --> 02:33.616
these parent-child reunions
can get intense.

02:33.617 --> 02:35.234
Chairs might be thrown.

02:35.235 --> 02:36.652
Weaves might be pulled.

02:36.653 --> 02:37.937
Or I could just go in there,

02:37.938 --> 02:40.106
show him how awesome I am,
no thanks to him,

02:40.107 --> 02:41.057
meet my half-brother...

02:42.025 --> 02:43.909
And then, boom.
Closure.

02:43.910 --> 02:45.628
Your dad has another son?

02:45.629 --> 02:47.063
Yeah.
So, clearly, he's moved on.

02:47.064 --> 02:48.964
Why can't I?
Close your mouths.

02:48.965 --> 02:50.566
Look, I appreciate
your concern,

02:50.567 --> 02:52.918
but really, the most helpful
thing you can do

02:52.919 --> 02:54.286
is stay out of my business.

02:54.287 --> 02:56.205
Oh, can you
say that last part again?

02:56.206 --> 02:58.257
These walls
are entirely too thick.

02:58.258 --> 03:00.459
♪ Give me some rope

03:00.460 --> 03:02.178
♪ tie me to dream

03:02.179 --> 03:03.495
♪ give me the hope

03:03.496 --> 03:05.331
♪ to run out of steam

03:05.332 --> 03:08.634
♪ somebody said
it can be here ♪

03:08.635 --> 03:10.352
♪ we could be roped up

03:10.353 --> 03:12.688
♪ tied up, dead in a year ♪

03:12.689 --> 03:17.810
♪ I can't count the reasons
I should stay ♪

03:17.811 --> 03:21.847
♪ one by one,
they all just fade away ♪

